==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tuyre
<hw>Tu`y⟦egrave⟧re"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.; akin
to <ets>tuyau</ets> a pipe; of Teutonic origin. Cf. <er>Tweer</er>,
<er>Tewel</er>.]</ety> <def>A nozzle, mouthpiece, or fixture through
which the blast is delivered to the interior of a blast furnace, or to
the fire of a forge.</def> <altsp>[Corruptly written also
<asp>tweer</asp>, and <asp>twier</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tuy⟦egrave⟧re arch</b></col>, <cd>the embrasure, in the
wall of a blast furnace through which the tuy⟦egrave⟧re
enters.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tuz</ent>⟦br⟧
